reviews.text: Its balcony overseeing Tsim Sha Tsui is the catchy spot. One can enjoy a beer or two prior to going indoor for dinner.
Good location, lovely food and fair price.
Great boutique with rooftop and excellent view of Victoria Harbour.

An alternative Dim Sum place in TST, especially when others are full during weekends. It occupies the top floor of a new commercial bldg on Observatory Road, with its own huge seaview patio for drinks/smoking. Food is acceptable though not outstanding but price very fair, more so considering its city center location.
Very nice view of Hong Kong island in the evening..
